Interested in being a substitute for Rolling Hills?

Please stop in Central Office (60851 Southgate Road Cambridge, OH 43725) Monday-Friday 8:00 a.m. - 3:30 p.m. and fill out an application. Ask for Allison if you have any questions or need assistance with the application process.

Substitute Nurse* $11.95/hour
Substitute Cook $8.70/hour
Substitute Paraprofessional* $8.70/hour
Substitute Custodian $8.70/hour
Substitute Secretary $8.70/hour
Substitute Bus Driver* $14.50/hour

*Proper licensing and credentials required.
ALL applicants must have a current, clear BCI and FBI background check.

Parents, Guardians and Students,

First day for students will be September 1, 2020. It is recommended that all students wear face masks in school. Face masks are mandatory on all school busses. School will be in-class instruction Tuesday-Friday. Monday’s will be remote learning and students will remain home.

Students will have the option to attend school in person or use the remote learning option.

More information will be available after the school board meeting on Thursday 7-23-20 at 6:30 PM.

Thank you for your understanding as we process these uncharted waters. GO COLTS!

shared_text:
Muskingum Valley Health Centers
July 15 at 10:00 AM ·

We're getting closer to the launch of our partnership with Rolling Hills Local School District for the new MVHC Rolling Hills Health Center!

MVHC Rolling Hills Health Center will provide complete healthcare and behavioral health services to students during school hours. The School-Based Health Center will also provide care to the community after school hours by appointment. MVHC Rolling Hills Health Center will operate Monday-Friday and is scheduled to open this August.

Our School Health Program is centered on providing comprehensive primary care services including pediatric, adolescent, and behavioral health care to students. This community-based model of care is designed to provide affordable, age-appropriate, confidential, convenient care to students. MVHC medical staff and providers will treat illness, as well as providing preventative care and well-child services.

Muskingum Valley Health Centers
June 18 at 3:30 PM ·

MVHC + Rolling Hills School District

We are excited to announce our partnership with Rolling Hills School District creating the MVHC Rolling Hills Health Center!

MVHC Rolling Hills Health Center will be located behind Brook Elementary in Byesville to provide complete healthcare and behavioral health services to students during school hours. The School-Based Health Center will also provide care to the community after school hours by appointment. MVHC Rolling Hills Health Center will operate Monday-Friday and is scheduled to open this August.

Our School Health Program is centered on providing comprehensive primary care services including pediatric, adolescent, and behavioral health care to students. This community-based model of care is designed to provide affordable, age-appropriate, confidential, convenient care to students. MVHC medical staff and providers will treat illness, as well as providing preventative care and well-child services.

post_text:
The Rolling Hills Local School District is excited to announce their partnership with Muskingum Valley Health Centers. This partnership will include a School-Based Health Center located behind Brook Intermediate to provide complete healthcare and behavioral health services to our students during school hours. This location will also be available to the community after school hours by appointment.

For more information or to request a School Link Health Services Consent packet for you children, please call 740-432-5370 or email allison.garner@rollinghills.k12.oh.us. Packets can also be picked up at Central Office M-F 8AM-2PM.

The Center is scheduled to open in August and we are very excited to provide our students and community with such resources. It is a great time to be a Colt!

Please keep an eye on your mailbox and your SNAP/EBT cards. Your kids may be receiving additional pandemic EBT benefits, even if you have never received EBT benefits before. If you receive a P-EBT card in the mail in your child's name DO NOT THROW IT AWAY! This is not a scam, this is a real benefit from the USDA to help you pay for all of the missed meals from the end of the school year.

To make the most of your P-EBT benefits take them find a Produce Perks location near year and use them there to get DOUBLE your produce dollars. You can get UNLIMITED produce perks dollars through June 30th 2020. Produce Perks DO NOT EXPIRE and can be used anytime at any participating Produce Perks location.…

post_text:
NAME: Samantha Scharenberg

PLANS AFTER GRADUATION: Muskingum University, Art Therapy

WHAT THEY MISS ABOUT THEIR SENIOR YEAR: What I miss about Meadowbrook is being around friends, still learning something new every day and the staff. Meadowbrook staff has definitely been great to me, they have all helped in so many ways and have taught me never to give up on something you truly believe in. Especially Mr.Baker, he always tried to help me be my best! To all the staff, I’d like to thank you all for making my high school experience so much fun!

A MESSAGE FROM ROLLING HILLS STAFF & COMMUNITY: “Samantha Scharenberg always has a smile on her face and is always friendly and the first to speak when you see her in the hall. She has come through some difficulties and major challenges during her high school career but it has never changed her approach or upbeat attitude. We are all very proud of Sam and excited to see what she continues to accomplish.”

NAME: Angel Cross

ACTIVITIES AND GROUPS: FFA

PLANS AFTER GRADUATION: I plan on going to midway for adult classes so I can get certified in welding. After I get certified I plan on trying to find a welding job locally so I can get the experience I need to be able to go to the pipeline for welding.

WHAT THEY MISS ABOUT THEIR SENIOR YEAR: I miss being able to see all my friends and just being at school in general. I miss all the teachers I was close too.

A MESSAGE FROM ROLLING HILLS STAFF & COMMUNITY: “Angel came to our school not knowing anyone. She took a risk in taking my class and found friendships that will last a lifetime. In the past two years I have had the opportunity to see her grow, learn new things and meet new people. Whether it be our talks on life, the next trip, or classes, I will miss having Angel there to talk to. “

post_text:
NAME: Joe Whealdon

GROUPS AND ACTIVITIES: I have been involved in National Honor Society for 3 years and am currently serving as Secretary. I have been serving on the Blood Committee for 2 years and I have been in DECA and FFA for one year each. I am a one year letterman in Cross Country and have been throwing in track for 2 years.

PLANS AFTER GRADUATION: My Primary plan is to attend the United States Merchant Marine Academy in Kings Point, New York and major in Maritime Logistics and Security. Upon graduation I will fulfill my service obligation in the US Navy. My backup plan is to enlist in the Navy.

WHAT THEY MISS ABOUT THEIR SENIOR YEAR: I miss seeing my friends.

A MESSAGE FROM ROLLING HILLS STAFF & COMMUNITY: “I have teased Joe Whealdon for years about being an old man in a teenage body, and it is a fact. Joe is an old soul, but he owns it. He is calm, sensible, smart and dependable, and he will do great things with these qualities.”

SENIOR SPOTLIGHT

NAME: Baylee Harmon
ACTIVITIES AND GROUPS: FCA, Cross Country, Volleyball, Basketball, Track

PLANS AFTER GRADUATION: I plan on attending OUZ to study math education.

WHAT THEY MISS THE MOST ABOUT THEIR SENIOR YEAR: I miss my friends, my teachers, and getting to enjoy the last of my senior year.

A MESSAGE FROM ROLLING HILLS STAFF TO OUR SENIOR: “I've loved watching her grow so much in the last couple of years. She's tried out so many new things this year - and has grown every step of the way! She's overcome a lot and really started to learn that she can do anything she puts her mind to. I'm so proud to know her and can't wait to see how God continues to work in her life!” "Always nice to talk to and driven in my class. Fun to have conversations with and was always a joy to see. She will be missed by me and I'm sure, others."

A MESSAGE FROM ROLLING HILLS STAFF TO OUR SENIOR: I've loved watching Brayden grow up the last few years. I can't believe he's graduating!! SENIOR SPOTLIGHT

NAME: Jaden Valentine

ACTIVITIES AND GROUPS: Volleyball, FCA, NHS, and the MVL Leadership Team

PLANS AFTER GRADUATION:I plan to attend Ohio University Zanesville to pursue a degree in Nursing.

WHAT THEY MISS THE MOST ABOUT THEIR SENIOR YEAR:While being out of school, the thing I miss the most about Meadowbrook is seeing our teachers and staff every day. They never failed to make me smile, even during the bad days.

A MESSAGE FROM ROLLING HILLS STAFF TO OUR SENIOR: "Where do I even start with this girl? She's so kindhearted and comes from one of the best families. I love that I get to be a part of her life outside of school/volleyball. I love her hard work, I love her determination. I love her love for other people and her willingness to do anything for other people. She's smart, she's talented, she's compassionate! She's rooted in her faith and her beliefs and I'm so proud of the young woman she is and the young woman she's going to become."

PLANS AFTER GRADUATION:I plan to attend Ohio University Zanesville to pursue a degree in Nursing.

WHAT THEY MISS THE MOST ABOUT THEIR SENIOR YEAR:While being out of school, the thing I miss the most about Meadowbrook is seeing our teachers and staff every day. They never failed to make me smile, even during the bad days.

A MESSAGE FROM ROLLING HILLS STAFF TO OUR SENIOR: "Where do I even start with this girl? She's so kindhearted and comes from one of the best families. I love that I get to be a part of her life outside of school/volleyball. I love her hard work, I love her determination. I love her love for other people and her willingness to do anything for other people. She's smart, she's talented, she's compassionate! She's rooted in her faith and her beliefs and I'm so proud of the young woman she is and the young woman she's going to become."

SPECIAL ANNOUNCEMENT FOR ROLLING HILLS FAMILIES:

The Rolling Hills Local School District and Stop 9 Church of Christ will be offering a “Weekend Snack Box” for RHLSD families. The Stop 9 Church of Christ currently provides snacks for over 80 students in our district. Our students depend on the daily meals we provide and often have limited access to food over the weekends. In order to combat childhood hunger, we are teaming up to continue providing non-perishable snacks for our families with children.

Donated snacks may be dropped off to the Church Monday through Thursdays from 9:30 am to 4:00 pm., under the carport at the church. Boxes will be passed out on Thursdays from 3:00-6:00 pm…

Applicants must be able to pass a background check. Certain certifications required.

A huge THANK YOU to our friends at Ascent Resources for supplying our 3rd, 4th and 5th grade classes with their school supplies for the 2019-20 school year!

Parents of a 3rd, 4th or 5th grader- PLEASE attend the Brook Intermediate Open House Wednesday August 14th at 6:00 PM to pick up your students school supplies (excluding the optional trapper keeper for 5th grade) and say thank you to this generous company! A OneCall will also be sent for families without social media but please help spread this great news!

We are excited for our students and are thankful for the great community we have here in Colt Nation!

“ The grant is designed to have 3 different aspects that will work together but all have a different focus. The first part is focused on stress management. It features a large floor weaving loom that is designed to make rugs. The process of weaving on the loom involves your entire body. Weaving on such a loom allows one to really get rid of aggression. Prepping material for the loom involves ripping fabric. What could be more stress…
